claim.claim-text:
An engine controller comprising:
a circuit board (12) for controlling an engine;
an aluminum die-cast main case body (20) having an open top for housing the circuit board (12); and
a covering member (30) made of an iron-based metal plate which is preliminarily applied with surface treatment, such as a plated steel plate, the covering member (30) being fixedly clamped, to the main case body (20) by means of a setscrew (40) so as to hermetically close the open top of the main case body (20);
wherein the main case body (20) is provided, at the open top thereof, with a pedestal (24) or groove (25) on which a liquid or jellied water-proofing adhesive (50) is coated or filled, thereby enabling entire outer peripheral edge face of the covering member (30) to be substantially covered by the water-proofing adhesive (50) coated or filled on the pedestal (24) or groove (25), thus hermetically sealing the interior of the main case body (20).

An engine controller comprising:
a circuit board (12) for controlling an engine;
an aluminum die-cast main case body (20) having an open top for housing the circuit board (12); and
a covering member (30) made of an iron-based metal plate which is preliminarily applied with surface treatment, such as a plated steel plate, the covering member (30) being fixedly clamped to the main case body (20) by means of a setscrew (40) so as to hermetically close the open top of the main case body (20);
wherein a liquid or jellied water-proofing adhesive (50) is provided between the main case body (20) and the covering member (30) circumferentially internally of a fixedly clamped portion where the covering member (30) is clamped to the main case body (20) by means of the setscrew (40), so as to hermetically seal the interior of the main case body (20), and wherein a liquid or jellied water-proofing adhesive (50) is provided also between the main case body (20) and the covering member (30) circumferentially externally of the fixedly clamped portion where the covering member (30) is clamped to the main case body (20) by means of the setscrew (40), so as to hermetically seal the fixedly clamped portion.
